President Muhammadu Buhari has arrived at Ogun State on a one-day official visit to inaugurate some projects undertaken by Governor Dapo Abiodun. Buhari, clad in agbada made with the popular local Adire fabrics, arrived at the Gateway City Gate Monument, Sagamu-Interchange-Abeokuta at 11.37am in the company of Abiodun. Buhari was received by the governors of Yobe, Ekiti, Ondo and Osun states. The President had already inaugurated the 14km Ijebu-Ode – Epe road expressway, which connects Ogun to Lagos State. Buhari will proceed to inaugurate the 42km Sagamu Interchange–Abeokuta dual carriageway, which is now renamed as the President Muhammadu Buhari expressway. Other projects scheduled for commissioning are the new Kobape Housing Estate, located on the Sagamu-Abeokuta Interchange, and the first phase of Kings Court Estate, Abeokuta, developed by the Ogun State Property and Investment Corporation. The President, during his visit, will also attend a town hall meeting where he is expected to interact with stakeholders and leaders of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the State.